{
  "stem": "25639.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was bewildering, confusing, degrading.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, our parents said that we should-- we should stay with Jewish kids, that perhaps it will be safer because sometimes Jewish boys were beaten up.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Girls-- I haven't heard in our town about girls, but boys got into fights because they fought back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were taught to defend themselves and protect themselves.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I was not taught to fight back, and girls just weren't.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had-- we could tell each other off, verbally, but we would not attack each other.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I, I have never seen that in my town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I'm sure it must have happened, but I, I don't recollect any such event.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And of course, as time went on, we had to start wearing the yellow star.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Only because my father was a hero during World War I in the Austria-Hungarian empire, and he had six medals to show for it, he was excused from-- he and his family was excused from wearing the yellow star.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there is a document that I made a copy of that my brother had-- and I will be glad to share that with you-- which states that David Hollander and his family are excused from wearing the yellow star because he was a hero in World War I, as you know, fighting on the German side.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And what's interesting about this is that, that-- we have a picture.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And what's interesting about this is that, that, in World War I, they fought on the side of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And of course, they lost.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But then came World War II, and both my father and his brothers were taken to the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And my father is the sole survivor of that Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
